<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAR 93 / Observer: Cartoon capers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A year after Punch folded, The Cartoonist comes into being. Although it is
being launched on April 1, the fortnightly broadsheet newspaper is no joke.
Backed by the upmarket Coutts, with a handful of small shareholders, it will
have an initial print-run of 100,000 and a cover price of Pounds 1.20. But
says its publisher, John Sorrell: 'If we achieve a settle-down figure of
40,000, we'll be very happy'. He adds: 'We think it is a perfect time to be
launching. In a recession people are desperate for things to smile about.'
But what happens when the recession ends?
