<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Short-term truck rentals behind Dawsongroup
leap
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
INCREASING demand for short-term truck rental helped Dawsongroup, the
commercial vehicle concern, to multiply pre-tax profits more than four times
from Pounds 1.13m to Pounds 4.75m last year.
Mr Peter Dawson, chairman and chief executive, said: 'In recession, a large
number of vehicle operators have sought to defer capital investment and
long-term commitments by turning to short-term rental.'
The group invested Pounds 10.5m in new equipment for the short-term fleet.
Sales rose from Pounds 43m to Pounds 46.7m.
Rentals increased pre-tax profits from Pounds 982,000 to Pounds 4.2m on the
back of new contracts from companies no longer interested in long-term
contracts.
The commercial vehicles division increased pre-tax profits from Pounds
144,000 to Pounds 534,000. Sales rose only marginally and a large part of
the increase represented additional trucks sold to the group's rental
division.
Group operating profits rose from Pounds 6.26m to Pounds 8.99m. Net interest
fell to Pounds 4.2m (Pounds 5.1m).
Earnings per share increased to 10.4p (2.7p). The final dividend is raised
to 2.25p for an increased total of 3p (1.5p).
</TEXT>
