FT  25 MAR 93 / Blockade threat as fish talks fail
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FISHERMEN'S leaders yesterday threatened further blockades of UK ports in
protest at the European Community's fisheries policy.
The fresh warning came after talks between the National Federation of
Fishermen's Organisations and Mr David Curry, the fisheries minister, ended
in apparent deadlock. Mr Curry rejected calls for import controls,
particularly on cheap Russian fish. He said recent falls in prices had been
caused by oversupply from British boats and not by cheap imports, and UK
prices were now rising.
