<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAR 93 / Observer: No charge
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A mobile phone racket which has already confused the airwaves over Australia
and Sweden has hit London. High tech criminals who have pinched mobiles have
found a way of altering the in-built electronic security number so that the
bill goes to another user. Salesmen in long coats lined with phones are now
touting stolen state-of-the-art equipment around offices in London for
Pounds 260 apiece with the promise that they will be good for a year, no
charge.
Gives Freefone numbers a whole new meaning.
</TEXT>
