<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Revised dividends
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In the light of recent proposed Budget changes a number of companies
yesterday made dividend statements.
To comply with its Articles of Association, SmithKline Beecham has increased
its fourth quarter 1992 dividend on A shares from 2.375p to 2.533p.
London Forfaiting declared a second interim of 5.5p for 1992 in lieu of the
proposed 5.5p final already announced.
Sumit will pay a 1.4p interim in lieu of the proposed 1.4p final for 1992.
TT Group declared a second interim of 3.6p for the year to December 26 in
lieu of the 3.6p final forecast when it announced the offer for AB
Electronic Products last December.
